title: St. Pat's moves up a spot in C2 polls

Previous Next St. Pat's moves up a spot in C2 polls 
Aaron Allison (13), of St. Pat's, intercepts a ball in front of Southern Valley receiver J.T. Grilli in the second quarter of a 36-0 win for the Irish over the Eagles on Sept. 11 in North Platte. (Andrew Bottrell / The North Platte Telegraph) Posted: Tuesday, October 20, 2015 2:10 pm St. Pat's moves up a spot in C2 polls Telegraph staff reports nptelegraph.com 
St. Pat’s moved up to No. 7 in the Class C2 Associated Press poll heading into their final game of the season against Bayard (2-6) on Friday. 
The Irish continued to roll last week with a 62-8 win over Cambridge. The Irish have not lost since the first week of the season and are allowing 4.8 points per game to their opponents during their seven-win streak.   Need an account? Create one now. Subscription required
